.TH "skb_copy_and_csum_datagram_msg" 9 "skb_copy_and_csum_datagram_msg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
skb_copy_and_csum_datagram_msg \- Copy and checksum skb to user iovec.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" skb_copy_and_csum_datagram_msg
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "int hlen "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *msg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
skbuff
.IP "hlen" 12
hardware length
.IP "msg" 12
destination

Caller _must_ check that skb will fit to this iovec.
.SH "RETURN"
0       - success.
-EINVAL - checksum failure.
-EFAULT - fault during copy.
